# spac (https://github.com/.../spac) — substring allowlist for vendored Archon fixtures.
# Each non-comment line is a literal substring. Any finding snippet containing the
# line is suppressed. Keep substrings narrow so real secrets aren't accidentally
# whitelisted.

# Vendored Archon smoke-fixture comment that mentions the env-var NAME (not a value).
# File: packages/studio-fixtures/src/round-trip-fixtures/_smoke-pi-all-nodes.yaml
# False-positive: spac's keyword pattern matches `Auth:` + high-entropy token,
# capturing `Auth: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (the env-var NAME, not a value).
# Whitelisting this exact match-snippet is safe — a REAL secret in the form
# `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...` would still trip the high-confidence pattern
# `\bsk-ant-...\b` independently of this allowlist entry.
Auth: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
